    <div class="section">
        <h2>Inflatoria - World Design</h2>
        <div class="setting-card">
            <h3>🏢 The Air Pump Station</h3>
            <p>Bureaucratic nightmare with towering helium dispensers, pin-filled security systems, and sadistic balloon-headed clerks who get off on the power of controlling air supply.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="setting-card">
            <h3>🌆 Neon District</h3>
            <p>Pulsing nightlife zone with "Pure Air" dealers, underground balloon-popping raves, and dart-throwing gangs marking territory with deflated balloon corpses.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="setting-card">
            <h3>☁️ Sky Rehab</h3>
            <p>Floating treatment center in the clouds for balloon-heads with severe deflation depression or inflation addiction. Run by uptight rubber doctors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="setting-card">
            <h3>🎪 The Twist Factory</h3>
            <p>Where animal-shaped balloons like Zeppy originated. Now an abandoned industrial wasteland filled with failed balloon experiments and twisted metal.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Episode Structure Template</h2>
        <div class="episode-structure">
            <h3>🎬 Cold Open (30 seconds)</h3>
            <p>Quick gag or setup showing characters in their natural chaos - usually someone's about to pop, deflate, or get high.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="episode-structure">
            <h3>⚡ Inciting Incident (1 minute)</h3>
            <p>The crew faces a problem that requires them to venture into Inflatoria's dangerous landscape. Usually involves drugs, bureaucracy, or gang activity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="episode-structure">
            <h3>🌪️ Escalating Chaos (3-4 minutes)</h3>
            <p>Plan goes wrong, strings get tangled, someone nearly pops, psychedelic sequences, and increasingly desperate solutions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="episode-structure">
            <h3>💥 Climax (1 minute)</h3>
            <p>Maximum visual chaos - explosions, string physics, balloon heads in extreme states, reality warping.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="episode-structure">
            <h3>🌈 Resolution (30 seconds)</h3>
            <p>Problem "solved" but usually with new complications. Characters share drugs/helium while the world glitches into psychedelic patterns.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Animation Principles</h2>
        <p><strong>Balloon Physics:</strong> Heads react realistically to air pressure - creaking when stressed, sagging when sad, bobbing with movement. String dynamics are crucial for both comedy and symbolism.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Rubbery Movement:</strong> All motion has a slight bounce and stretch. Characters move like they're made of living rubber, with exaggerated squash-and-stretch principles.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Environmental Response:</strong> Backgrounds pulse and warp based on the emotional intensity of scenes. Colors shift from scene to scene, sometimes mid-conversation.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Drug Sequences:</strong> Reality breaks down completely - characters become fractals, the world melts, impossible geometry, time dilation effects.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Sound Design Notes</h2>
        <p>🎵 <strong>Musical Palette:</strong> Distorted electronic beats, warped trap influences, helium-pitched vocals, rubber squeaking as percussion</p>
        <p>🔊 <strong>Balloon SFX:</strong> Creaking rubber for tension, squeaks for movement, sharp pops for violence, hissing air for deflation/drugs</p>
        <p>📻 <strong>Voice Processing:</strong> Characters' voices change with their balloon state - higher when inflated, lower when deflated, distorted when popped</p>
        <p>🎪 <strong>Environmental Audio:</strong> Industrial helium machinery, neon buzzing, street noise with balloon-specific elements (pop gunshots, air leaks)</p>
    </div>
</div>
```

